Document: UPNPDevice
Path: godot/classes/class_upnpdevice.rst
Summary: Provides an interface for interacting with UPnP devices on the local network.

UPNPDevice

Inherits: Object < Object

This class provides an interface for interacting with UPnP devices on the local network. It allows you to discover devices, query their capabilities, and manage port mappings.

Key Rule: UPnP functionality is only available on the host operating system.

Methods:
add_device_blocked(device: UPNPDevice)
Adds a device to the blocked list. Devices in the blocked list will not be considered for port mapping.

get_gateway_device() → UPNPDevice
Returns the gateway device, if one is available. The gateway device is typically the router on the local network.

get_service(device: UPNPDevice, service_type: String) → UPNPService
Returns the UPNPService with the given service type from the specified device.

is_device_blocked(device: UPNPDevice) → bool
Checks if the given device is in the blocked list.

remove_device_blocked(device: UPNPDevice)
Removes a device from the blocked list.

search_gateway()
Searches for a gateway device on the local network. This method should be called before attempting to use any other UPnP functionality.

search_devices()
Searches for UPnP devices on the local network.

Signals:
device_added(device: UPNPDevice)
Emitted when a new UPnP device is discovered.

device_removed(device: UPNPDevice)
Emitted when a UPnP device is removed from the network.

device_blocked_added(device: UPNPDevice)
Emitted when a device is added to the blocked list.

device_blocked_removed(device: UPNPDevice)
Emitted when a device is removed from the blocked list.
