Document: UPNPDevice
Path: godot/classes/class_upnpdevice.rst
Summary: Provides low-level access to UPNP control commands for managing port mappings and querying network information.
UPNPDevice is a Universal Plug and Play (UPnP) device. It offers low-level access to UPnP control commands, enabling the management of port mappings (port forwarding) and the querying of network information such as local and external IP addresses and status. Note that methods on this class are synchronous and block the calling thread.
---CHUNK---
Document: UPNPDevice
Path: godot/classes/class_upnpdevice.rst
Summary: This section details the properties of the UPNPDevice class, including URLs, addresses, service types, and IGD status.

Properties:
* description_url (String): The URL for the device's description. Default: ""
* igd_control_url (String): The control URL for the IGD (Internet Gateway Device) service. Default: ""
* igd_our_addr (String): The IP address of the IGD. Default: ""
* igd_service_type (String): The service type of the IGD. Default: ""
* igd_status (IGDStatus): The current status of the IGD connection. Default: 9
* service_type (String): The service type of the UPnP device. Default: ""
